The epitope sequence has homology only with sequences from M. leprae proteins; no sequence similarities were found with any other sequences deposited in the current databases, including other mycobacteria. The epitope has predicted binding motifs to HLA Class II (DRB1*0101, 0701, 0801) and HLA Class I (B40, B*5401, B8, B61, B62) alleles.

column12: This structure constitutes the hexaarabinofuranosyl termini of the arabinan as found in mycolylarabinogalactan-peptidoglycan complex and lipoarabinomannan of the mycobacterial cell wall. The lipoarabinomannan used in this study was isolated from the from M.smegmatis, while the one used for immunizations was from M.leprae.

The PIM<sub>6</sub> component of lipoarabinomannan of the cell wall of mycobacterium species can have other lipidic moieties. In this study, upon deacylation of M.leprae PIM palmitic and tuberculostearic acids are said to be released, so those lipids are depicted in the structure.
